ss I tap into Scala's compiler toolbox, which could complicate things.\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Defining Test Code for ZIO**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI’m thinking about defining test code that invokes public macro APIs from ZIO through the added dependency to `zio_3` while ensuring it's properly set up. It seems like the artifact `zio-internal-macros_3` might only include renderers and ANSI. I need sufficient functional coverage, particularly for ANSI, and I’m wondering if the `TerminalRendering` main method is present. Upon checking, it looks like there isn’t a main method in the source for version 2.1.20, which makes me question how version 2.1.19 was compiled.\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"toolCall\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"call_z04pPifqWeQW1t8n5mcZoZvG|fc_018c650981dfa3020169fa6e39683c81a08286669120bca718\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"bash\\\", \\\"arguments\\\": {\\\"command\\\": \\\"javap -classpath ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/dev.zio/zio-internal-macros_3/2.1.20/cdbace847f5fac6d15e52b2db721833391199e3d/zio-internal-macros_3-2.1.20.jar 'zio.internal.TerminalRendering$' | sed -n '1,220p'\\\"}}], \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-responses\\\", \\\"provider\\\": \\\"OCA\\\", \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.5\\\", \\\"usage\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 789, \\\"output\\\": 626, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 29184, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"totalTokens\\\": 30599, \\\"cost\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 0, \\\"output\\\": 0, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 0, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"total\\\": 0}}, \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"toolUse\\\", \\\"timestamp\\\": 1778019885645, \\\"responseId\\\": \\\"resp_018c650981dfa3020169fa6e2e75f481a082307c0ad7f20387\\\"}}\\n2104:[recv] {\\\"type\\\": \\\"turn_end\\\", \\\"message\\\": {\\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"thinking\\\", \\\"thinking\\\": \\\"**Navigating Scala and Java Restrictions**\\\\n\\\\nI’m facing some issues with using Scala and Java together, especially with access restri